Where does the whistle-blower rest? People also hope to see the admonition of Li Wenliang and others can be corrected, so that paid a huge price of the "whistle-blower" can be justified.

This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

From The economist print edition

Editor in Chief | Bin Chen

On the night of February 6,2020, hundreds of millions of Internet users across China stayed up all night praying for Dr. Li Wenliang. A number of journalists, including this newspaper's, were waiting at Wuhan's Central Hospital.

The doctor in Wuhan, known as the "whistle-blower" of the new pneumonia outbreak, was infected with the virus earlier. After he was critically ill, news of his death spread late on the 6th, and it was said that he was still being treated. At 0:38 on the 7th, his Home Hospital in Wuhan Central announced on Weibo that he was "critically ill and in full rescue. ". At 03:48, Wuhan Central Hospital again posted on Weibo, "we deeply regret and mourn the death of Li Wenliang at 2:58 a.m. on February 7. ".

This News, let countless people shed tears, countless people sad.

Dr. Lee's early warning of the disaster, and his subsequent suffering, touched the hearts of millions. On December 30,2019, Dr. Li Wenliang, an ophthalmologist at Wuhan Central Hospital, announced in a group of about 150 students that seven patients with confirmed SARS (later corrected to coronavirus infection) had been admitted under isolation in the hospital's emergency department, remind the students who work in Wuhan Hospital to take precautions. Screenshots of his remarks were posted outside the group and circulated widely on the Internet.

But late that night, he was called by the Wuhan Health Commission to inquire about the situation, the next day and was interviewed by the hospital supervision section. On January 3,2020, Li Wenliang was again admonished by the police station for "spreading rumors" . But as it turned out, what Dr. Li said was not a rumor.

After being admonished, Dr. Li Wenliang did not lose heart, continued to work in the front line, dutifully, unfortunately in a few days after work infected with the virus, hospitalized. When reporters interviewed him on January 30, he had already checked into the intensive-care unit, but told reporters that he would still be on the front line after his recovery.

Dr. Li said in an interview that he did not care whether he could be exonerated because "the truth is the most important thing. ". True enough. It is because of his speech that new crown pneumonia has attracted wide public attention. If we can face up to the epidemic from then on and take decisive measures, the pneumonia epidemic will not get out of control to this point. But there is no "if. ". Wuhan then "dealt with" eight doctors who "spread rumors" through the public security organs, allowing the public and decision-making levels to underestimate the severity of the epidemic, resulting in such a severe situation in Wuhan, the country was also greatly affected.

On Jan. 29, the Supreme Court discussed rumors at the legal level in a post on the official wechat account. The article said that the so-called "rumors" (legally called false information) originated from the limitations of individual cognitive ability, but also from the information of the public is not timely and opaque. To solve the rumor problem, the disclosure of information is the radical cure. If government information is released in a timely and accurate manner, rumors will lose their market. If, on the other hand, "rumor" is proved to be a "far-ahead prediction" time and time again, people will naturally choose to believe rumors in the face of unexpected events. The article says that it is neither legally necessary nor institutionally possible to attempt a legal attack on all information that does not fully conform to the facts, and that it may even lead us to strike the rumor as the opposite of the value of legal justice, become a negative example to undermine the credibility of the government.

This is the existence of the "whistle-blower" for the whole society immeasurable value and significance. If time could be turned back, if Dr. Li Wenliang's early warning of the outbreak had been promptly responded to and measures taken, would new pneumonia not have developed into such a grave situation, how much suffering could have been avoided? And to what extent has Dr. Li's admonition, defined by the Public Security Bureau as "giving false information, " damaged public trust in the region and caused more chaos?

It was Dr. Li Wenliang's brave speech that tore open a corner of the curtain and drew the attention of some members of the public to the epidemic in the early days.

Our condolences to Dr Li Wenliang. His voice and his face are forever in that moment. What's the use of not having a father? His children have lost their father, his unborn child will never see his father, and his wife, parents and family have lost the family tree. His death is not a statistical one, but a tragedy of life, which has been counted in the hundreds and counting.

We thank Dr. Li Wenliang for his first whistle based on professionalism and kindness. We must also bear in mind the enormous cost to society of the failure of the whistle to be transmitted in time. Hope that this price can be real reflection and progress, this is Dr. Lee with his professional honor and life to practice the truth.

The Wuhan City Government issued a notice on February 7 to express condolences and respect for Li Wenliang, but the admonition is still there, "whistle blower" how to rest? People also hope to see the admonition of Li Wenliang and others can be corrected, so that paid a huge price for the "whistle-blower" can be justified.

Wenliang Wenliang, a person contains and issued by the light of civilization, will always illuminate us. Dr Li Wenliang!
